   Janino by janino-compiler .syntaxHighlighter.xml { padding: 6px 12px 6px 12px; line-height: 1em; } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .plain { color: #b9bdb6; } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .spaces { } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .keyword { color: #5ba1cf; } Janino A super-small, super-fast Java compiler View the Project on GitHub janino-compiler/janino Download ZIP File Browse JAVADOC View On GitHub Breaking news! Janino is now "Tee-ware", which means that the applicable license is still BSD, but you are free to buy a fan t-shirt on Teespring (one per CPU, or as many as you want 😉). Support the software development and show your appreciation by purchasing Janino merch! Janino is a super-small, super-fast Java compiler. Janino can not only compile a set of source files to a set of class files like JAVAC, but also compile a Java expression , a block , a class body , one .java file or a set of .java files in memory, load the bytecode and execute it directly in the running JVM. JANINO is integrated with Apache Commons JCI ("Java Compiler Interface") and JBoss Rules / Drools. JANINO can also be used for static code analysis or code manipulation . Table of Contents Getting Started Properties Requirements Limitations License Download Packages Security / integrity Installation Examples Documentation Change Log JAVADOC Books Links Basic Examples Janino as an Expression Evaluator Janino as a Script Evaluator Janino as a Class Body Evaluator Janino as a Simple Compiler Janino as a Compiler Advanced Examples
