e documentation. If there's a compile failure related to the library, I might need to provide guidance without suggesting a code strategy.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on library setup**\\n\\nI need to analyze whether the library requires additional setup beyond the regular test scaffold for meaningful coverage. The setup could fall into one of three categories: an extra Maven dependency, a Docker image, or specific environment/system properties that the tests should configure. I'll categorize the dependencies and Docker images as deterministic setups while placing any environment variables or properties in agent guidance. If my research doesn't reveal a need for extra setup, I’ll choose no action.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"Janino 3.1.0 is a self-contained Java compiler library; its required commons-compiler dependency is declared transitively, and meaningful coverage is reachable through public Janino APIs without extra Maven dependencies, Docker, or environment setup. The observed javac failure is from an obsolete internal package import, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The removed org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator.Iterables type appears under org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator in the transitive commons-compiler artifact; tests should avoid relying on the old internal Janino package.\",\n    \"Native-image execution of Janino dynamic compilation may still hit inherent dynamic class-loading/runtime classpath limitations, but that is a test-design/native-image limitation rather than a setup prerequisite.\",\n    \"Optional Ant integration would require org.apache.ant:ant, but it is optional/provided and not needed for normal Janino compiler, expression, script, or simple-compiler coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e270f421d4f6e6b016a42c4566c68819582628e5a382fb5d1\",\"phase\":\"